1. HTML to define the content of web pages

2. CSS to specify the layout of web pages

3. JavaScript to program the behavior of web pages


Document Object Model:(DOM)Application programming interface

\\JavaScript can "display" data in different ways:

1)Writing into an HTML element, using innerHTML.
2)Writing into the HTML output using document.write().
3)Writing into an alert box, using window.alert().
4)Writing into the browser console, using console.log().

Using document.write() after an HTML document is loaded, will delete all existing HTML:
You cannot access output devices from JavaScript.
The only exception is that you can call the window.print() method in the browser to print the 
content of the current window.

example for defferentiationg let and var:
{                                                      
  var x = 2;
}
// x CAN be used here
{
  let x = 2;
}
// x can NOT be used here


var i = 5;
for (var i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
  // some statements
}
// Here i is 10


let i = 5;
for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
  // some statements
}
// Here i is 5